      • close

        public void close()
        Description copied from class: RepositorySession
        Close the session. Required to be called for all open sessions to ensure resources are properly released. If the session has been marked as dirty, it will be saved. This may save partial changes in the case of a typical try { ... } finally { ... } approach - if this is a problem, ensure you revert changes when an exception occurs. can throw RuntimeException
